1
00:00:14,906 --> 00:00:17,787
Oh wow! The cherry blossoms are in full bloom!

2
00:00:18,079 --> 00:00:20,918
Flower viewing at a shrine is wonderful, isn't it?

3
00:00:21,001 --> 00:00:23,507
Yeah, and the weather is perfect, too.

4
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:25,594
It's truly ideal weather for flower viewing.

5
00:00:25,677 --> 00:00:28,350
My stomach's having its own feast-weather day!

6
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,354
Oh, Genta-kun...

7
00:00:30,437 --> 00:00:33,735
Ha ha ha! Truly a case of "dumplings over flowers," huh?

8
00:00:33,819 --> 00:00:34,862
Hm?

9
00:00:36,866 --> 00:00:40,874
Well then, Professor, we're going to go draw some fortunes.

10
00:00:40,958 --> 00:00:43,755
Could you save our spot and lay out the tarp?

11
00:00:43,839 --> 00:00:45,342
Mhm, will do.

12
00:00:45,425 --> 00:00:47,262
Alright, let's go!

13
00:00:47,346 --> 00:00:48,473
Wish us luck!

14
00:00:48,557 --> 00:00:50,435
Conan-kun, we're going!

15
00:00:50,519 --> 00:00:51,563
Yeah.

16
00:00:52,523 --> 00:00:54,151
What?
Hm?

17
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:55,904
Looking for someone?

18
00:00:56,113 --> 00:00:58,827
Ah, no... not really.

19
00:01:02,668 --> 00:01:08,680
♪~

20
00:01:15,652 --> 00:01:19,368
Black shadows and dark darkness,
The light of deduction cuts right through.

21
00:01:19,452 --> 00:01:22,750
Information tangles beneath the cherry blossoms,
A strange case and the FBI.

22
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:24,629
See through to the one single truth.

23
00:01:24,712 --> 00:01:26,341
Looks like a child, mind of an adult.

24
00:01:26,591 --> 00:01:29,347
His name is Detective Conan!

25
00:02:46,417 --> 00:02:52,429
~♪

26
00:02:55,469 --> 00:03:01,169
"In Reminiscence of Jodie and the Trap of Flower Viewing"

27
00:03:08,016 --> 00:03:10,729
Ugh... Bad fortune, of all things...

28
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:13,192
I got Good Fortune!

29
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,820
Ayumi got Fairly Good Fortune.

30
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:17,576
I got Slight Fortune, so it's a bit mixed, huh?

31
00:03:17,868 --> 00:03:20,123
Then let's all go tie ours on the rack!

32
00:03:20,206 --> 00:03:21,250
Yeah!
Okay!

33
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:23,921
Now, now, hold on.
Huh?

34
00:03:24,006 --> 00:03:27,637
Since you drew good fortunes, you should take them home with you.

35
00:03:28,181 --> 00:03:29,641
Tying up fortunes

36
00:03:29,725 --> 00:03:31,437
is only for when you want to leave bad luck behind

37
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,816
and turn your luck around, you see.

38
00:03:34,151 --> 00:03:37,616
Ah, these days people just tie up anything and everything —

39
00:03:37,699 --> 00:03:40,538
kind of a bad habit that's caught on, really.

40
00:03:40,622 --> 00:03:41,665
Wow~

41
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:45,715
So then, is Edogawa-kun the only one who should tie his up?

42
00:03:45,799 --> 00:03:48,471
She was totally peeking at mine...

43
00:03:48,805 --> 00:03:51,268
...So, what'd you draw?

44
00:03:51,352 --> 00:03:52,939
Oh? You wanna know?

45
00:03:53,022 --> 00:03:54,817
N-Not really...

46
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,489
If you're that curious, I guess I have no choice.

47
00:03:57,905 --> 00:03:59,281
Great Fortune:
"Proceed forward without forcing things, and happiness will come your way.
Matters will resolve naturally if you consult with others.
Your worries will dissipate, and things will conclude well."

48
00:03:59,618 --> 00:04:01,122
G-Great Fortune?!

49
00:04:01,205 --> 00:04:02,499
Heh heh.

50
00:04:03,209 --> 00:04:04,586
Wow, Ai-chan!

51
00:04:04,670 --> 00:04:06,132
I'm so jealous!

52
00:04:06,215 --> 00:04:08,302
Wanna trade for mine?

53
00:04:08,971 --> 00:04:11,600
But, I hear that drawing Bad Fortune is actually pretty rare

54
00:04:11,684 --> 00:04:13,813
and can be a sign of good luck in reverse,

55
00:04:14,481 --> 00:04:16,652
so don't be too disappointed, Cool Kid.

56
00:04:16,735 --> 00:04:18,531
Jodie-sensei!
Heh heh.

57
00:04:18,614 --> 00:04:21,036
Ah!
Jodie-sensei!

58
00:04:21,745 --> 00:04:22,831
Hi~!

59
00:04:22,914 --> 00:04:25,378
Sensei, did you come for flower viewing, too?

60
00:04:25,461 --> 00:04:29,636
Oh, yes! I love cherry blossoms, after all.

61
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:31,390
I see.
Hm?

62
00:04:32,017 --> 00:04:36,400
So, you called sensei here for a secret chat between the two of you, huh?

63
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:37,694
Huh...?

64
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:39,781
They say parks and shrines

65
00:04:39,865 --> 00:04:43,581
are places spies and the like often use to exchange information.

66
00:04:44,082 --> 00:04:47,172
Come on, everyone, let's give them some space.

67
00:04:47,422 --> 00:04:50,762
Seems like they want to have a private, secret talk.

68
00:04:50,845 --> 00:04:52,098
Oh... uh...
Hm?

69
00:04:52,891 --> 00:04:54,979
But, well, at the same time—

70
00:04:55,063 --> 00:04:58,361
they're also places where the Public Security Police are keeping a close watch,

71
00:04:58,444 --> 00:05:00,323
so do be very careful.

72
00:05:00,823 --> 00:05:02,244
O... Okay.

73
00:05:05,917 --> 00:05:09,007
So... what did you want to talk to me about?

74
00:05:09,091 --> 00:05:10,093
Well.

75
00:05:10,385 --> 00:05:11,720
Before, sensei—

76
00:05:11,804 --> 00:05:15,061
you mentioned seeing Akai-san with burn scars, right?

77
00:05:15,144 --> 00:05:16,480
Ah... yes.

78
00:05:16,940 --> 00:05:19,653
During that bank robbery case...

79
00:05:22,534 --> 00:05:23,744
Ah...!

80
00:05:28,170 --> 00:05:29,423
Shu?

81
00:05:32,554 --> 00:05:34,766
W-Wait a minute...

82
00:05:35,184 --> 00:05:36,437
Shu!

83
00:05:38,024 --> 00:05:41,155
Oh, sorry... ha...

84
00:05:44,244 --> 00:05:45,371
Ha...

85
00:05:49,296 --> 00:05:50,340
Shu...

86
00:05:51,342 --> 00:05:52,385
Shu!

87
00:05:53,179 --> 00:05:57,187
Is it you, Shu? It is you, Shu, right?! Say it's you, Shu!

88
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:01,904
Ah...!

89
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,868
The burn scars...

90
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:08,584
That guy...
Hm?

91
00:06:09,127 --> 00:06:11,548
That guy wasn't Akai-san—

92
00:06:11,632 --> 00:06:16,266
he was a man called Bourbon, one of the Black Organization guys, in disguise.

93
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:17,769
What?!

94
00:06:18,104 --> 00:06:21,402
To confirm whether Akai-san was really dead,

95
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:26,078
he was hanging around Akai-san's acquaintances in that form.

96
00:06:26,495 --> 00:06:30,628
Because if the FBI was faking his death, he'd be able to tell from their reactions.

97
00:06:30,963 --> 00:06:33,426
Well, during the Bell Tree Express case—

98
00:06:33,884 --> 00:06:37,684
it seems like Vermouth herself, who'd disguised him as Akai-san,

99
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:40,565
was the one impersonating Akai-san then.

100
00:06:40,815 --> 00:06:45,658
Huh? Th... the Bell Tree Express... that train bombing too—

101
00:06:45,908 --> 00:06:47,829
was that their doing?

102
00:06:52,881 --> 00:06:55,428
Yeah, looks that way.

103
00:06:56,138 --> 00:06:57,557
Wait a minute.

104
00:06:57,849 --> 00:07:01,648
If that burned guy was one of their allies...

105
00:07:02,484 --> 00:07:04,488
then as I thought, Shu is...

106
00:07:05,698 --> 00:07:06,993
really...

107
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:14,716
Then, next time that burned guy shows his face,

108
00:07:14,799 --> 00:07:18,390
we'll grab him, rip off his disguise, and expose who he really—

109
00:07:18,474 --> 00:07:20,061
I've already got that covered.

110
00:07:20,144 --> 00:07:21,188
Huh?

111
00:07:21,271 --> 00:07:23,400
His whereabouts, too.
What?!

112
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:26,657
He's going by the name Toru Amuro,

113
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:29,621
and he's working part-time at the Poirot coffee shop

114
00:07:29,704 --> 00:07:30,915
below the Mouri Detective Agency.

115
00:07:30,999 --> 00:07:32,544
Wh... why?

116
00:07:32,627 --> 00:07:36,510
Who knows... That's why I asked you to come, sensei.

117
00:07:36,593 --> 00:07:39,599
I want the FBI to look into that.

118
00:07:39,683 --> 00:07:42,855
Why is he still staying at Poirot

119
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:45,403
when his objective should have already been achieved?

120
00:07:45,695 --> 00:07:46,905
Objective?

121
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,325
Ah, well, that's...

122
00:07:48,409 --> 00:07:49,996
Huh?
Hm?

123
00:07:50,329 --> 00:07:52,125
Excuse me, aren't you—

124
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:55,381
the foreign woman who was taken hostage with us

125
00:07:55,464 --> 00:07:57,552
during that bank robbery?

126
00:07:57,635 --> 00:07:58,804
Huh?
- Benzaki Touhei (35), Cherry blossom viewer

127
00:07:59,014 --> 00:08:00,224
Actually, I—

128
00:08:00,308 --> 00:08:03,063
I was diagonally behind you at that time,

129
00:08:03,147 --> 00:08:04,316
and the one who put duct tape

130
00:08:04,399 --> 00:08:07,905
over your eyes and mouth was my wife...

131
00:08:07,990 --> 00:08:09,409
Do you remember?

132
00:08:09,492 --> 00:08:10,954
(Coughing)

133
00:08:11,204 --> 00:08:13,709
Ah, yes... vaguely...

134
00:08:14,127 --> 00:08:15,588
So, by any chance—

135
00:08:15,671 --> 00:08:19,888
was that man with the burn scars next to you back then your boyfriend or...?

136
00:08:20,514 --> 00:08:23,604
He's not. What about it?

137
00:08:23,687 --> 00:08:26,526
Ah, no... it's nothing, then.

138
00:08:27,028 --> 00:08:29,032
It's just that I spotted him two or three days ago.

139
00:08:29,115 --> 00:08:30,117
Huh?

140
00:08:30,534 --> 00:08:32,372
Where? Where did you see him?!

141
00:08:33,374 --> 00:08:35,378
Answer me!
Eh... huh?

142
00:08:35,461 --> 00:08:39,511
A pickpocket! There's a pickpocket!

143
00:08:39,844 --> 00:08:42,350
Oww... ouch ouch...

144
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:43,477
Are you alright?

145
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:45,398
Are you okay, ma'am?

146
00:08:45,898 --> 00:08:49,614
Yes... Someone had their hand in my bag just now—

147
00:08:49,698 --> 00:08:50,908
I panicked.

148
00:08:51,326 --> 00:08:54,499
It's true, crowds like this have a lot of pickpockets.

149
00:08:54,582 --> 00:08:55,584
Yes...

150
00:08:55,793 --> 00:08:57,755
Ah!
Huh?

151
00:08:58,048 --> 00:09:01,263
Uh... yes. That's very true.
- Yatani Ikuyo (50). Cherry blossom viewer.

152
00:09:01,346 --> 00:09:03,642
We really do need to be careful, don't we?

153
00:09:04,394 --> 00:09:06,273
Well then, excuse us.

154
00:09:12,410 --> 00:09:14,789
(Bell sound)

155
00:09:19,841 --> 00:09:23,432
No, Genta-kun, you can't drink that water!

156
00:09:23,515 --> 00:09:25,436
Huh? Really?

157
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:29,068
You just rinse your mouth lightly and spit it out on the ground.

158
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:31,823
So... still can't remember?

159
00:09:32,158 --> 00:09:33,995
Where you met him?

160
00:09:34,078 --> 00:09:38,587
Yeah... I was knocked out with a cold all day yesterday, so my memory is...

161
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:41,009
(Coughing)

162
00:09:41,092 --> 00:09:43,388
His voice is really hoarse, huh?

163
00:09:43,472 --> 00:09:46,938
So, mister, you wanna gargle with this water too?

164
00:09:47,021 --> 00:09:50,903
No, I'll pass. I don't want to give you my cold,

165
00:09:50,987 --> 00:09:53,242
and I already purified my hands earlier.

166
00:09:53,325 --> 00:09:57,250
Could it be you spotted him in front of a canned coffee vending machine somewhere?

167
00:09:57,333 --> 00:09:58,585
Does he... like canned coffee?

168
00:09:58,669 --> 00:10:01,758
Is that it? Him?

169
00:10:01,842 --> 00:10:03,262
(Coughing)

170
00:10:03,512 --> 00:10:05,891
Yes, he drank it often.

171
00:10:06,309 --> 00:10:10,025
Yeah... even back then, when it seemed like they were about to attack the hospital

172
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:11,486
at any moment.

173
00:10:13,866 --> 00:10:16,246
Hey, Shu...
Hm?

174
00:10:16,329 --> 00:10:18,542
Have you seen that guy before somewhere?

175
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:21,381
He's one of the investigators added to the team this time.

176
00:10:21,464 --> 00:10:25,014
Who knows... I'm not good with allies' faces.

177
00:10:25,514 --> 00:10:27,768
But an enemy's face, I wouldn't forget.

178
00:10:29,522 --> 00:10:32,486
Well, it's only natural that he looks familiar.

179
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:35,117
He's an FBI agent, same as us.

180
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,202
Right.

181
00:10:36,912 --> 00:10:41,129
But... whenever I look at him, I get an uneasy feeling...

182
00:10:45,387 --> 00:10:47,141
Ah!
Hm?

183
00:10:53,904 --> 00:10:55,074
Shu...

184
00:10:56,826 --> 00:11:01,461
Y... You must have been tired, to drop your canned coffee like that.

185
00:11:01,544 --> 00:11:03,131
...Wait, did you say "attack"?

186
00:11:03,215 --> 00:11:05,552
Ah, no, no!

187
00:11:05,636 --> 00:11:08,392
That guy and the burned guy are different people!

188
00:11:08,475 --> 00:11:09,519
Oh...

189
00:11:09,852 --> 00:11:13,987
Forget it. If you remember, will you contact me here?

190
00:11:14,070 --> 00:11:15,531
Ah... yes.

191
00:11:16,908 --> 00:11:18,453
Something's off.

192
00:11:18,912 --> 00:11:21,042
Inside the Bell Tree Express,

193
00:11:21,126 --> 00:11:25,050
Bourbon was saying he was convinced Akai-san was dead—

194
00:11:25,969 --> 00:11:29,517
so why would he need to disguise himself as Akai-san again?

195
00:11:30,561 --> 00:11:33,400
What on earth for...?

196
00:11:46,928 --> 00:11:51,145
You can't do that, Genta-kun! You shouldn't ring it so violently!

197
00:11:51,228 --> 00:11:55,237
But, y'know, my dad says these things should be done with gusto...!

198
00:11:55,321 --> 00:11:57,325
That's right!
Huh?

199
00:11:57,617 --> 00:12:00,831
(Bell sound)

200
00:12:01,875 --> 00:12:03,086
That bell—
- Danno Yoriko (29), cherry blossom viewer.

201
00:12:03,169 --> 00:12:05,048
it's a bell to let the gods know

202
00:12:05,131 --> 00:12:06,551
you've come here.

203
00:12:06,635 --> 00:12:08,389
So, if you don't ring it a whole bunch,

204
00:12:08,472 --> 00:12:10,476
the gods might not notice you, you know?

205
00:12:10,726 --> 00:12:13,022
Wow!
So that's it!

206
00:12:13,106 --> 00:12:16,988
Alright! Let's do this with a bang!

207
00:12:17,072 --> 00:12:20,413
(Bell sound)

208
00:12:20,496 --> 00:12:21,915
Hey...
Hm?

209
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,840
This Akai person you were talking about earlier... what's he like?

210
00:12:25,923 --> 00:12:26,925
Why?

211
00:12:27,301 --> 00:12:32,018
Somehow... I get the feeling he's a lot like someone I know.

212
00:12:32,311 --> 00:12:36,903
I-Isn't it just your imagination? Besides, Akai-san is already...

213
00:12:36,987 --> 00:12:39,284
Wait, he's dead?!
Huh?

214
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:40,995
Ah...
Seriously?!

215
00:12:41,078 --> 00:12:44,544
Ah, they said there's a huge commotion behind the restrooms.

216
00:12:44,919 --> 00:12:46,673
Let's go check it out!
Yeah!

217
00:12:46,756 --> 00:12:50,347
(Cell phone ringtone)
Ah...

218
00:12:50,431 --> 00:12:52,268
Professor? What's up?

219
00:12:52,643 --> 00:12:56,025
Th-This is terrible, Shinichi! It's murder!

220
00:12:56,108 --> 00:12:59,407
It seems I have witnessed a murder!

221
00:12:59,866 --> 00:13:03,373
What?! You witnessed a murder?

222
00:13:03,457 --> 00:13:05,294
What?!
Anyway, just hurry and get over here!

223
00:13:05,377 --> 00:13:07,673
Quite a crowd of onlookers has gathered,

224
00:13:07,757 --> 00:13:09,928
so you'll find the place right away.

225
00:13:14,312 --> 00:13:15,773
Over there, huh?

226
00:13:18,946 --> 00:13:21,660
So? Did you see the culprit?

227
00:13:21,743 --> 00:13:24,039
I only saw a silhouette in the shade of the trees,

228
00:13:24,122 --> 00:13:28,047
but they were beating the victim repeatedly with a stick about 30 centimeters long.

229
00:13:28,465 --> 00:13:31,846
A stick about 30 centimeters long... beaten to death, then.

230
00:13:35,061 --> 00:13:37,900
E-Excuse me... move aside, move aside.

231
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,696
Ah!
Ah...

232
00:13:44,079 --> 00:13:45,499
This person...

233
00:13:47,085 --> 00:13:48,714
Ah!
No way...

234
00:13:48,964 --> 00:13:52,053
Isn't this the lady who bumped into sensei earlier?!

235
00:13:52,137 --> 00:13:53,139
Why...

236
00:13:53,932 --> 00:13:57,063
Doesn't look like much time has passed since she was killed.

237
00:13:57,857 --> 00:13:58,859
Hm?

238
00:13:59,319 --> 00:14:02,073
A 5-yen coin painted black with magic marker...

239
00:14:02,658 --> 00:14:04,036
Kurobe, huh?

240
00:14:04,579 --> 00:14:05,623
Kurobe?

241
00:14:06,249 --> 00:14:07,960
It's a pickpocket's nickname.

242
00:14:08,044 --> 00:14:12,678
They slip three black 5-yen coins into the pocket of the person they've robbed,

243
00:14:12,762 --> 00:14:14,056
so they're called that.

244
00:14:14,432 --> 00:14:16,143
Why would they do that?

245
00:14:16,226 --> 00:14:18,315
Rumor is it's a play on words.

246
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:22,990
The 5 of the 5-yen coin, the black of the magic marker, three coins...

247
00:14:23,074 --> 00:14:25,371
"Go, Kuro, San"

248
00:14:25,454 --> 00:14:27,583
meaning "Thanks for the hard work earning money

249
00:14:27,667 --> 00:14:29,796
so I could steal it from you," or so they say.

250
00:14:30,213 --> 00:14:31,883
Ah, officer! Over here, over here!

251
00:14:31,966 --> 00:14:33,470
Hm?
Professor!

252
00:14:33,553 --> 00:14:38,020
Hm... What's this? You kids, get away from the body.

253
00:14:38,104 --> 00:14:41,778
I'm an FBI agent.

254
00:14:41,861 --> 00:14:43,072
Jodie Starling.

255
00:14:43,448 --> 00:14:45,327
Huh... FBI?

256
00:14:45,411 --> 00:14:48,375
Seal off all the entrances and exits of this shrine immediately!

257
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:49,752
Call in the detectives!

258
00:14:49,836 --> 00:14:51,464
Y-Yes, ma'am!

259
00:14:51,965 --> 00:14:55,012
So, you don't mean... the culprit is this Kurobe?

260
00:14:55,096 --> 00:14:59,020
No... The fact that the coin purse this woman had in her pocket

261
00:14:59,104 --> 00:15:02,361
is packed full of black 5-yen coins...

262
00:15:02,903 --> 00:15:06,828
means this lady herself was probably Kurobe.

263
00:15:07,036 --> 00:15:08,038
What?!

264
00:15:08,122 --> 00:15:10,919
This bundle of bills inside her billfold,

265
00:15:11,003 --> 00:15:13,592
wrapped with a rubber band...

266
00:15:14,050 --> 00:15:15,304
Inside is...

267
00:15:15,387 --> 00:15:17,850
This is a GPS transmitter?

268
00:15:17,933 --> 00:15:19,562
A... transmitter?

269
00:15:19,645 --> 00:15:23,027
Using your cell phone, you can pinpoint its location within a 5-meter margin of error.

270
00:15:23,110 --> 00:15:25,866
S-Something like that, wrapped up in bills,

271
00:15:25,949 --> 00:15:28,497
inside a pickpocket's wallet, would mean...

272
00:15:28,955 --> 00:15:30,876
Yeah, probably—

273
00:15:30,959 --> 00:15:34,759
the victim who had their wallet stolen by Kurobe is the murderer.

274
00:15:34,842 --> 00:15:36,513
Ha!
What?!

275
00:15:41,104 --> 00:15:43,527
This puts us in a bind, Jodie-san.

276
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:47,660
No matter if you're an FBI agent, this is Japan.

277
00:15:47,743 --> 00:15:51,793
And on top of that, you're visiting Japan on vacation, right?

278
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:56,928
If you go giving orders during an investigation on your own, the honor of us Japanese police...

279
00:15:57,011 --> 00:16:01,312
I'm sorry. My usual habits just kicked in.

280
00:16:01,396 --> 00:16:04,944
But this crime scene is far from the shrine's entrances,

281
00:16:05,027 --> 00:16:07,198
and the body hadn't been dead

282
00:16:07,283 --> 00:16:10,079
for very long since the murder, so...

283
00:16:10,162 --> 00:16:12,501
thanks to sealing the shrine entrances,

284
00:16:12,835 --> 00:16:15,214
the culprit should be trapped inside.

285
00:16:15,299 --> 00:16:17,218
Right, Conan-kun?

286
00:16:17,303 --> 00:16:18,305
Yeah.

287
00:16:18,388 --> 00:16:20,099
No, well...

288
00:16:20,182 --> 00:16:23,273
It's certainly true your timely instructions were a big help.

289
00:16:23,356 --> 00:16:25,485
But is that really true?
Oh?

290
00:16:25,569 --> 00:16:28,700
Hm?
That this woman who was beaten to death

291
00:16:28,783 --> 00:16:33,083
is the pickpocket Kurobe, who Third Division has been pursuing for years?

292
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:35,422
I'm pretty sure there's no mistake.

293
00:16:35,505 --> 00:16:38,720
Inside the coin purse that lady was carrying,

294
00:16:38,803 --> 00:16:42,728
it was packed full of 5-yen coins painted black with magic marker.

295
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:46,486
It's true that Kurobe apparently put

296
00:16:46,569 --> 00:16:49,659
three black 5-yen coins into the pocket of the person she robbed, but...

297
00:16:49,742 --> 00:16:52,581
Hmm... So...

298
00:16:52,665 --> 00:16:54,794
is it true that you witnessed this Kurobe

299
00:16:54,877 --> 00:16:57,508
being beaten to death? Professor Agasa?

300
00:16:57,591 --> 00:16:58,969
Ah... yes.

301
00:16:59,387 --> 00:17:01,014
I had finished up in the restroom,

302
00:17:01,098 --> 00:17:04,689
and when I passed by here, I saw it, but—

303
00:17:04,772 --> 00:17:06,734
it's dark here in the shade of the trees,

304
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:10,492
so at first I thought they might be pounding in a stake or something.

305
00:17:10,784 --> 00:17:12,830
So, what about the culprit's face?

306
00:17:12,913 --> 00:17:15,377
It was mostly just a silhouette, you see.

307
00:17:15,919 --> 00:17:18,215
I could tell they were wearing a hat

308
00:17:18,299 --> 00:17:22,599
and holding a thin stick about 30 centimeters long, but...

309
00:17:22,891 --> 00:17:26,315
I see. So that is the murder weapon.

310
00:17:26,399 --> 00:17:28,903
Were there any other distinguishing features?

311
00:17:28,987 --> 00:17:30,449
Let's see...

312
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:33,872
Oh, now that you mention it, when the culprit was leaving,

313
00:17:33,955 --> 00:17:36,586
they were dragging their leg just a little bit.

314
00:17:36,669 --> 00:17:39,508
Enough that I even called out, "Are you alright?"

315
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,637
Dragging their leg?

316
00:17:41,721 --> 00:17:43,349
And then what about the culprit?

317
00:17:43,850 --> 00:17:46,104
They ignored me and left,

318
00:17:46,188 --> 00:17:51,031
and by the time I realized the person they'd been beating was that woman,

319
00:17:51,114 --> 00:17:52,910
they were already into the crowd.

320
00:17:52,993 --> 00:17:54,120
I see.

321
00:17:54,914 --> 00:17:58,880
Inspector, in that situation, wanting to leave as quickly as possible,

322
00:17:58,963 --> 00:18:01,134
if they were dragging their leg...

323
00:18:01,218 --> 00:18:02,513
Hmm...

324
00:18:02,596 --> 00:18:06,604
It doesn't seem likely it was an act to get removed from the suspect list...

325
00:18:06,687 --> 00:18:10,654
But based on that alone, from among the huge crowd of flower viewers

326
00:18:11,113 --> 00:18:13,535
who came to this shrine...

327
00:18:13,952 --> 00:18:16,791
singling out the murderer would be nearly impossible.

328
00:18:16,874 --> 00:18:19,338
I think we can narrow it down much more.

329
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:23,053
There was something strange inside that lady's billfold.

330
00:18:23,137 --> 00:18:25,224
Ah... something strange?

331
00:18:25,559 --> 00:18:28,565
A GPS transmitter wrapped up in bills.

332
00:18:28,815 --> 00:18:30,861
Wh... why would something like that be in there?

333
00:18:30,944 --> 00:18:34,243
If that pickpocket Kurobe had never been caught before,

334
00:18:34,535 --> 00:18:38,208
you wouldn't be able to identify Kurobe until after your pocket was picked

335
00:18:38,293 --> 00:18:40,630
and those black 5-yen coins were slipped into your pocket.

336
00:18:40,714 --> 00:18:44,680
So, they deliberately let a wallet with a transmitter inside get stolen,

337
00:18:44,763 --> 00:18:46,642
tracked its location with a cell phone,

338
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:51,193
waited for Kurobe to go somewhere deserted, and beat her to death.

339
00:18:51,569 --> 00:18:55,702
S-So, the victim Kurobe robbed is the murderer?!

340
00:18:55,785 --> 00:18:58,791
But pickpocketing often involves multiple accomplices,

341
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:02,382
so we can't dismiss the possibility of a falling out among thieves, either...

342
00:19:02,466 --> 00:19:03,468
That's true.

343
00:19:03,968 --> 00:19:06,766
I think Kurobe was working alone, though.

344
00:19:06,849 --> 00:19:09,730
She herself yelled, "There's a pickpocket!"

345
00:19:09,813 --> 00:19:11,692
Huh? What do you mean?

346
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:14,281
It's a common trick pickpockets use.

347
00:19:14,365 --> 00:19:18,539
When you hear "There's a pickpocket!" you instinctively check your own wallet, right?

348
00:19:19,165 --> 00:19:23,258
That's how the pickpocket learns where the target's wallet is, but—

349
00:19:23,341 --> 00:19:27,724
if she had a partner, she'd have had that partner play the role of shouting the warning, right?

350
00:19:28,309 --> 00:19:31,064
So, probably, Jodie-sensei's wallet, too...

351
00:19:31,147 --> 00:19:32,149
Huh?

352
00:19:32,693 --> 00:19:35,615
Ah! My wallet is gone!

353
00:19:36,074 --> 00:19:40,625
Most likely, she lifted it when you helped that person up after she fell.

354
00:19:43,046 --> 00:19:45,885
Sigh... Still, though—

355
00:19:45,969 --> 00:19:48,433
if the very person who stole it is dead,

356
00:19:48,683 --> 00:19:52,816
how are we supposed to go about finding the pickpocket victims...?

357
00:19:52,899 --> 00:19:54,486
In that case, probably soon...

358
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:55,947
(Detective Boys badge ringtone)
Hm?

359
00:19:56,031 --> 00:19:57,451
Hm?

360
00:19:59,078 --> 00:20:01,166
Conan-kun, we found it!

361
00:20:02,084 --> 00:20:06,510
The location is the trash can placed next to the fortune-tying area!

362
00:20:06,594 --> 00:20:08,264
I found one, too!

363
00:20:09,223 --> 00:20:12,981
In the trash can near the water purification basin!

364
00:20:13,065 --> 00:20:14,818
Ah! Looks like they found it!

365
00:20:15,987 --> 00:20:18,993
Inside the trash can at the bell-ringing spot!

366
00:20:19,077 --> 00:20:21,916
The shrine priest is getting it out for us now!

367
00:20:22,793 --> 00:20:26,634
Over here, it's in the trash can past the crime scene restrooms!

368
00:20:26,717 --> 00:20:30,809
I had to insist they let us search through trash that was about to be collected.

369
00:20:31,101 --> 00:20:33,021
Alright! Then bring the wallets you found

370
00:20:33,105 --> 00:20:35,192
without getting your fingerprints on them!

371
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:37,239
Alright!
Understood.

372
00:20:37,322 --> 00:20:39,326
I see! Wallets!
Huh?

373
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:43,041
Pickpockets take only the money from the wallets they steal and toss the rest,

374
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:45,922
so if we examine the contents of those wallets...

375
00:20:46,005 --> 00:20:49,763
In other words, we might be able to identify the wallet owners!

376
00:20:49,847 --> 00:20:51,559
Yes!
Heh.

377
00:20:53,019 --> 00:20:54,356
Hmm...

378
00:20:55,065 --> 00:20:58,573
Are these four the only wallets you found in the trash cans?

379
00:20:58,656 --> 00:21:02,873
Yes. The collection worker said they'd just started picking up

380
00:21:02,956 --> 00:21:04,751
from the trash cans I checked.

381
00:21:04,835 --> 00:21:07,841
Ah! That blue wallet... it's mine!

382
00:21:07,924 --> 00:21:10,137
Well then, that makes you one of the suspects.

383
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:11,265
Huh?

384
00:21:11,348 --> 00:21:13,478
Jodie-sensei couldn't have done it!

385
00:21:13,561 --> 00:21:17,903
After that lady bumped into her, she was with us the whole time!

386
00:21:17,986 --> 00:21:20,575
There wasn't any time for her to kill someone!

387
00:21:20,658 --> 00:21:22,704
Huh? I-Is that so?

388
00:21:23,372 --> 00:21:24,583
(Clears throat)

389
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:26,670
Which means the murderer...

390
00:21:26,754 --> 00:21:29,091
is highly likely among the owners

391
00:21:29,175 --> 00:21:31,305
of the remaining three wallets.

392
00:21:31,388 --> 00:21:32,641
Hmm...

393
00:21:33,893 --> 00:21:37,859
Oh? We can identify the owner of this black wallet right away.

394
00:21:38,361 --> 00:21:40,615
There's a driver's license inside.

395
00:21:40,698 --> 00:21:43,579
Oh! I saw this old guy earlier!

396
00:21:43,663 --> 00:21:44,706
Huh?

397
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:47,671
He's the one who came up and spoke to Jodie-sensei!

398
00:21:47,754 --> 00:21:50,468
He was wearing a mask, said he had a cold.

399
00:21:50,552 --> 00:21:52,472
I... I see.

400
00:21:54,351 --> 00:21:58,276
Seems only the black wallet had something with an ID, though.

401
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:00,613
Hm? A photo booth sticker?

402
00:22:00,697 --> 00:22:04,329
Ah! I know that lady, too!

403
00:22:04,413 --> 00:22:05,415
Huh?!

404
00:22:05,498 --> 00:22:08,337
She taught us how to ring the bell!

405
00:22:08,421 --> 00:22:10,925
She might still be around here somewhere!

406
00:22:11,009 --> 00:22:12,136
Hmm...

407
00:22:12,846 --> 00:22:15,685
Inside the last, red wallet...

408
00:22:16,979 --> 00:22:19,651
it just contains a Slight Fortune fortune slip.

409
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:23,784
I don't suppose we can identify this owner... Hm?

410
00:22:24,118 --> 00:22:26,665
Couldn't that wallet belong to that old man?

411
00:22:26,749 --> 00:22:29,463
He did tell us to take good fortunes home with us.

412
00:22:29,546 --> 00:22:31,800
Yes, and I saw it, too!

413
00:22:32,344 --> 00:22:33,471
Right in front of us,

414
00:22:33,554 --> 00:22:36,977
that old man took out a red wallet to buy a fortune!

415
00:22:37,227 --> 00:22:39,733
Ah! Ayumi saw that, too!

416
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:43,491
I thought it was a flashy wallet, not something you'd expect an old guy to have!

417
00:22:43,866 --> 00:22:45,703
Y-You can tell?

418
00:22:45,787 --> 00:22:48,626
Yeah!
Alright then, we'll go find him!

419
00:22:48,709 --> 00:22:50,212
Please wait here!

420
00:22:50,296 --> 00:22:54,178
H-Hey, you kids... The culprit could be a murderer, you know!

421
00:22:54,638 --> 00:22:57,142
Takagi-kun, go with the children!

422
00:22:57,226 --> 00:22:58,646
Ah... yes!

423
00:22:58,729 --> 00:23:02,278
Hmm... If one of those three were found

424
00:23:02,362 --> 00:23:06,160
to be carrying a stick about 30 centimeters long, it'd be settled, but...

425
00:23:06,245 --> 00:23:09,334
I think we'll know soon enough, even without them having it on them.

426
00:23:09,418 --> 00:23:12,590
Huh? What do you mean, Conan-kun?

427
00:23:12,674 --> 00:23:15,888
Because, the culprit, as if returning the favor,

428
00:23:15,972 --> 00:23:19,479
left three black 5-yen coins near the body.

429
00:23:19,563 --> 00:23:20,815
Huh?!

430
00:23:20,898 --> 00:23:23,320
Something as unique as these black 5-yen coins—

431
00:23:23,404 --> 00:23:26,117
they're not something you can just prepare so easily, right?

432
00:23:26,535 --> 00:23:29,416
I see! So, among those three,

433
00:23:29,499 --> 00:23:32,045
the one who doesn't have the black 5-yen coins

434
00:23:32,129 --> 00:23:34,551
that Kurobe should have slipped into their pocket— that person is the culprit!

435
00:23:35,010 --> 00:23:36,722
That's right.

436
00:24:03,736 --> 00:24:05,949
Wha— What is this about?

437
00:24:06,032 --> 00:24:09,038
A detective suddenly saying he wants to ask us some questions...

438
00:24:09,122 --> 00:24:10,584
(Coughing)

439
00:24:10,667 --> 00:24:13,423
Are you saying we've done something wrong?

440
00:24:13,715 --> 00:24:16,219
Before we get into that, first—

441
00:24:16,303 --> 00:24:19,267
could you please check your pockets or bags

442
00:24:19,351 --> 00:24:22,524
to see if they contain any 5-yen coins

443
00:24:22,608 --> 00:24:24,737
painted black with magic marker?

444
00:24:24,820 --> 00:24:27,158
5-yen coins painted black?

445
00:24:27,241 --> 00:24:28,953
What on earth is that?

446
00:24:29,037 --> 00:24:31,792
There's no way we'd have something so strange...

447
00:24:31,876 --> 00:24:33,086
(Sound of coins)
Ah!

448
00:24:34,088 --> 00:24:36,009
Why is something like this...?

449
00:24:36,259 --> 00:24:39,098
Found one! A black 5-yen coin.

450
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:40,602
Hmm...

451
00:24:40,685 --> 00:24:42,188
I have one as well.

452
00:24:42,271 --> 00:24:44,067
Me too...
Huh?

453
00:24:44,693 --> 00:24:46,071
Wha... This is...

454
00:24:46,364 --> 00:24:49,077
Hey, hey... all three of you have them?

455
00:24:49,578 --> 00:24:53,336
What on earth is this?! This creepy 5-yen coin?!

456
00:24:53,419 --> 00:24:57,761
W-Well, it's something like a calling card left by a pickpocket named Kurobe...

457
00:24:57,844 --> 00:25:01,686
What?! No way! So, I was pickpocketed?!

458
00:25:02,061 --> 00:25:05,652
As I thought... I just noticed my wallet was missing...

459
00:25:05,735 --> 00:25:07,322
(Coughing)

460
00:25:07,406 --> 00:25:09,743
I was just about to report it to the police.

461
00:25:10,077 --> 00:25:13,543
Well, there wasn't much in it anyway,

462
00:25:13,626 --> 00:25:15,380
so I wouldn't have minded letting them have it, but...

463
00:25:16,006 --> 00:25:17,926
Did you catch that pickpocket?

464
00:25:18,010 --> 00:25:19,930
No, well, about that...

465
00:25:20,014 --> 00:25:23,813
She was just found dead.

466
00:25:23,896 --> 00:25:24,940
What?!

467
00:25:25,692 --> 00:25:28,030
We suspect that among you three,

468
00:25:28,113 --> 00:25:30,410
the culprit is present.

469
00:25:30,493 --> 00:25:31,537
Huh?!

470
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:33,332
A-Among us?

471
00:25:33,416 --> 00:25:34,752
No way!

472
00:25:34,835 --> 00:25:37,089
Aren't we the victims?!

473
00:25:37,466 --> 00:25:40,638
For the time being, we'll conduct a body check on you three,

474
00:25:40,722 --> 00:25:43,936
and examine your belongings and cell phones.

475
00:25:44,020 --> 00:25:45,022
Huh?!

476
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:48,529
Of course, this is voluntary, so you can refuse, but...

477
00:25:48,613 --> 00:25:50,575
However, if you do refuse,

478
00:25:50,658 --> 00:25:52,954
I think it might lead to complications later on,

479
00:25:53,038 --> 00:25:55,877
so if at all possible...
Fine, alright!

480
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,964
If you want to check, go ahead and check!

481
00:25:58,341 --> 00:26:01,514
But in exchange, I have oily skin,

482
00:26:01,597 --> 00:26:03,976
so my phone is greasy, but just deal with it.

483
00:26:04,227 --> 00:26:05,270
Hah...

484
00:26:05,563 --> 00:26:07,526
Jodie-sensei?
Hm...

485
00:26:07,984 --> 00:26:09,738
Did you notice something?

486
00:26:09,822 --> 00:26:14,038
No... I just remembered the man in the video you shot for me before.

487
00:26:14,122 --> 00:26:15,875
I just remembered.

488
00:26:15,959 --> 00:26:20,677
You know, to identify the spy who infiltrated the hospital,

489
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:23,850
we purposely dropped the cell phone and had them pick it up, right?

490
00:26:23,933 --> 00:26:26,438
I was just thinking how that overweight man who picked it up first

491
00:26:26,522 --> 00:26:28,901
had oily skin.

492
00:26:28,985 --> 00:26:32,742
In the end, the man who picked it up next was the spy,

493
00:26:32,826 --> 00:26:35,790
and the last old man had a pacemaker.

494
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:40,007
And then Shu took that phone and...

495
00:26:41,385 --> 00:26:45,309
Hey, how about we transport him in that Beetle belonging to an older guy I know?

496
00:26:45,393 --> 00:26:46,437
Huh?

497
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:48,608
We can lay him down in the back seat,

498
00:26:48,691 --> 00:26:52,156
and those bad guys will probably think he's being moved in a large vehicle

499
00:26:52,239 --> 00:26:55,120
that can carry a stretcher,

500
00:26:55,204 --> 00:26:57,208
so I'm sure we won't be found out.

501
00:26:57,291 --> 00:26:59,630
W-Well, that may be true, but...

502
00:26:59,713 --> 00:27:02,969
I'll go outside and call him, then.

503
00:27:03,053 --> 00:27:04,890
I think he'll come right away.

504
00:27:04,973 --> 00:27:06,477
Ah, yeah...

505
00:27:07,102 --> 00:27:10,902
No matter how much of a boy wonder you are, that's something I can't agree to.

506
00:27:11,737 --> 00:27:14,200
This is our job, the FBI's.

507
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:20,087
We can't involve ordinary citizens any further than this.

508
00:27:20,170 --> 00:27:21,548
Ah, b-but...

509
00:27:22,509 --> 00:27:24,846
Leave the rest to us.

510
00:27:25,515 --> 00:27:27,727
H-Hey, Jodie-sensei...?

511
00:27:27,811 --> 00:27:29,188
Ah... Hah...

512
00:27:29,272 --> 00:27:32,027
S-Something like that... isn't really relevant right now, is it?

513
00:27:32,404 --> 00:27:35,952
Y-Yeah... I'm sorry.

514
00:27:36,035 --> 00:27:39,250
Finding out that burned man wasn't Shu... I've been

515
00:27:39,334 --> 00:27:42,089
a little shaken up, it seems.

516
00:27:42,340 --> 00:27:43,551
I need to pull myself together.

517
00:27:43,968 --> 00:27:46,014
What's wrong?
Ah.

518
00:27:46,097 --> 00:27:48,184
You suddenly raised your voice...

519
00:27:48,268 --> 00:27:52,360
Ah, no, it's nothing. Ha ha ha ha...

520
00:27:52,819 --> 00:27:53,988
Hm?

521
00:27:54,573 --> 00:27:56,660
So, what's the verdict, Professor?

522
00:27:56,744 --> 00:28:00,250
Among those three, is the culprit you saw there?

523
00:28:00,335 --> 00:28:01,378
Well...

524
00:28:01,670 --> 00:28:04,258
I suppose if I had to say, that old man with the cane is suspicious...

525
00:28:04,343 --> 00:28:07,056
but the culprit was holding a thin stick

526
00:28:07,139 --> 00:28:11,482
about 30 centimeters long.

527
00:28:11,565 --> 00:28:13,736
They didn't have a cane...

528
00:28:14,111 --> 00:28:16,115
The hat the culprit was wearing, too—

529
00:28:16,199 --> 00:28:20,333
it wasn't an old man's flat cap or a woman's knit cap,

530
00:28:20,416 --> 00:28:22,796
it looked more like a hiking hat.
(Coughing)

531
00:28:23,129 --> 00:28:27,764
And they weren't coughing like that man, either.

532
00:28:27,847 --> 00:28:31,980
But couldn't he just be pretending to have a cold?

533
00:28:32,064 --> 00:28:33,191
No, that's not it.

534
00:28:34,068 --> 00:28:36,573
At the point when we first met that guy,

535
00:28:36,657 --> 00:28:40,540
there's no way he knew we were acquainted with the Professor, right?

536
00:28:40,623 --> 00:28:45,383
So there'd be no need for him to pretend to have a cold in front of us.

537
00:28:45,466 --> 00:28:47,219
Well, that's true.

538
00:28:48,179 --> 00:28:51,353
So, Professor, what about the way they walked?

539
00:28:51,437 --> 00:28:54,651
You said they were dragging their leg a little, right?

540
00:28:55,026 --> 00:28:59,411
Hmm... That old man, rather than dragging his leg,

541
00:28:59,494 --> 00:29:02,500
seems like he truly can't stand without his cane.

542
00:29:03,209 --> 00:29:06,758
And the other two don't appear to be dragging their leg, either.

543
00:29:09,806 --> 00:29:12,562
What? You can't find the murder weapon?

544
00:29:12,979 --> 00:29:14,774
Did you search every inch?

545
00:29:14,858 --> 00:29:17,572
Yes. Inside the drainage ditch at the purification basin,

546
00:29:17,655 --> 00:29:19,951
and even inside the offering box, but...

547
00:29:20,703 --> 00:29:23,459
Those three didn't have it on them, right?

548
00:29:23,542 --> 00:29:26,840
Right. We also examined the old man's cane,

549
00:29:26,924 --> 00:29:29,429
but there were no signs it was used as a weapon.

550
00:29:29,513 --> 00:29:32,936
We also checked the three's cell phones,

551
00:29:33,019 --> 00:29:37,570
but none of the phones had any apps installed for tracking a transmitter.

552
00:29:37,987 --> 00:29:42,664
They might have anticipated being searched and deleted it, though.

553
00:29:42,747 --> 00:29:44,626
Yes, however...

554
00:29:44,709 --> 00:29:47,465
to investigate any further, we'll need a warrant.

555
00:29:47,924 --> 00:29:49,594
Hey, kids.

556
00:29:49,678 --> 00:29:53,894
When you met those three, did they act strangely at all?

557
00:29:53,978 --> 00:29:55,773
Act strangely?

558
00:29:56,065 --> 00:29:57,902
For example, if they had a companion

559
00:29:57,986 --> 00:30:01,493
and secretly handed them something like a long, thin stick?

560
00:30:01,910 --> 00:30:03,914
All three were alone.

561
00:30:03,998 --> 00:30:06,168
The old man told us if we drew a good fortune,

562
00:30:06,252 --> 00:30:09,300
we should take it home...

563
00:30:09,384 --> 00:30:14,018
And that lady told us to ring the bell loudly

564
00:30:14,101 --> 00:30:16,523
so the gods could hear us!

565
00:30:16,857 --> 00:30:19,278
The other man, at the purification basin—

566
00:30:19,362 --> 00:30:21,992
he said he'd already purified his hands,

567
00:30:22,075 --> 00:30:26,585
so it seems like he'd come to this shrine quite a while before he met us.

568
00:30:26,668 --> 00:30:28,087
Hmm...

569
00:30:28,171 --> 00:30:29,883
Inspector Megure!
Hm?

570
00:30:29,966 --> 00:30:33,139
We found what we believe are the culprit's hat and coat!

571
00:30:33,222 --> 00:30:34,559
Oh! Is that so?

572
00:30:35,268 --> 00:30:38,609
There's blood spatter on them, so we're fairly certain.

573
00:30:38,692 --> 00:30:42,282
Hmm... but they're covered in flower petals.

574
00:30:42,367 --> 00:30:46,917
Yes, they were hidden, covered by fallen cherry blossom petals.

575
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,337
What?

576
00:30:48,420 --> 00:30:51,677
Then the murder weapon might be hidden the same way!

577
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:53,931
Find it, even if you have to kick the petals aside!

578
00:30:54,223 --> 00:30:55,726
Yes, sir!

579
00:30:56,770 --> 00:31:01,488
What?! But it's such a beautiful pink carpet...

580
00:31:01,571 --> 00:31:05,663
That's right... Each piece is just a petal,

581
00:31:05,746 --> 00:31:09,421
but when so many are scattered, it's like a pink carpet.

582
00:31:09,504 --> 00:31:10,548
Yeah.

583
00:31:12,217 --> 00:31:15,014
I see... So that's it.

584
00:31:15,098 --> 00:31:18,522
That's why that person said that to the children.

585
00:31:19,524 --> 00:31:24,116
Which means, the reason the culprit was dragging their leg is probably...

586
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:28,834
It looks like you've grasped the truth of the case, but

587
00:31:29,126 --> 00:31:33,385
it seems you haven't quite arrived at the truth over here yet.

588
00:31:48,161 --> 00:31:50,625
Hey, how long are you planning to keep us here?!

589
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:53,004
The sun is already starting to set!

590
00:31:53,087 --> 00:31:55,843
I don't care if it's a case or whatever!

591
00:31:55,927 --> 00:31:58,097
This has nothing to do with us!

592
00:31:58,181 --> 00:32:01,521
S-Sorry... please, just bear with us a little longer.

593
00:32:01,605 --> 00:32:03,066
Inspector Megure!

594
00:32:03,149 --> 00:32:06,197
(Panting heavily)

595
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:09,621
Keeping the shrine entrances sealed is reaching its limit.

596
00:32:09,704 --> 00:32:10,706
I see.

597
00:32:11,123 --> 00:32:12,543
So, the murder weapon?

598
00:32:12,627 --> 00:32:16,510
Unfortunately, no report has come in yet that it's been found.

599
00:32:16,802 --> 00:32:19,808
Could it be that the culprit, still in possession of the murder weapon,

600
00:32:19,891 --> 00:32:22,981
has already escaped from this shrine...?

601
00:32:23,064 --> 00:32:27,907
No... Considering the time between the crime occurring and the sealing of the exits,

602
00:32:27,991 --> 00:32:31,748
and the fact the culprit was dragging their leg when leaving...

603
00:32:32,416 --> 00:32:36,424
It's highly likely the culprit is still within the shrine grounds.

604
00:32:36,675 --> 00:32:39,096
Having hidden somewhere the thin stick

605
00:32:39,179 --> 00:32:43,271
about 30 centimeters long that Agasa-san said he witnessed.

606
00:32:43,522 --> 00:32:45,609
Which means, as expected, the suspicious ones are—

607
00:32:45,693 --> 00:32:48,490
those three who were pickpocketed, right?

608
00:32:48,574 --> 00:32:49,576
Yeah.

609
00:32:50,076 --> 00:32:52,330
If a GPS transmitter wrapped in bills

610
00:32:52,414 --> 00:32:55,963
was inside the wallet of the pickpocket who was beaten to death...

611
00:32:56,882 --> 00:32:58,552
Just as Jodie-san said,

612
00:32:58,635 --> 00:33:02,518
we can only conclude that they deliberately let the wallet with the transmitter be stolen, tracked it,

613
00:33:02,602 --> 00:33:06,275
waited until she was in a deserted place, and beat her to death.

614
00:33:06,693 --> 00:33:08,447
But those three—

615
00:33:08,530 --> 00:33:11,285
none of them showed signs of having an injured leg.

616
00:33:11,368 --> 00:33:14,041
Besides, the old man, rather than injured,

617
00:33:14,124 --> 00:33:16,295
can't walk without a cane.

618
00:33:16,671 --> 00:33:19,844
And... if the culprit had an accomplice

619
00:33:19,928 --> 00:33:22,934
and secretly handed over the murder weapon...

620
00:33:23,017 --> 00:33:27,275
then we'd have to investigate every single flower viewer here at the shrine!

621
00:33:27,359 --> 00:33:28,695
There's no need for that.
Huh?

622
00:33:28,779 --> 00:33:29,948
There's no need for that.
Huh?

623
00:33:30,031 --> 00:33:34,081
Because the culprit is still carrying a part of the murder weapon, you see.

624
00:33:34,164 --> 00:33:35,501
Wh... A part of it?

625
00:33:35,793 --> 00:33:37,212
Ah, that's right.

626
00:33:37,295 --> 00:33:40,845
The culprit bundled those together to make the murder weapon.

627
00:33:40,928 --> 00:33:43,182
B... Bundled?

628
00:33:43,266 --> 00:33:46,773
But the weapon Agasa-san saw was a single stick, right?

629
00:33:46,857 --> 00:33:48,192
So, "bundled" or whatever...

630
00:33:48,569 --> 00:33:52,869
They bundled them together into one. A large quantity of something.

631
00:33:53,202 --> 00:33:55,791
And then, they hid it in a place

632
00:33:55,875 --> 00:33:59,006
where even if a lot of it was found, it wouldn't seem suspicious.

633
00:33:59,089 --> 00:34:00,968
They spoke to the children,

634
00:34:01,051 --> 00:34:03,807
cleverly using them as camouflage, you see.

635
00:34:03,891 --> 00:34:06,270
Huh?
T-To us?

636
00:34:06,730 --> 00:34:07,815
Then, could it be—

637
00:34:07,899 --> 00:34:10,738
the old man who spoke to us at the fortune place?

638
00:34:10,821 --> 00:34:14,244
Now that you mention it, there were tons of fortunes tied up there,

639
00:34:14,328 --> 00:34:16,917
so even if a few more were added, you wouldn't notice.

640
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:19,589
But no matter how you bundle fortunes together,

641
00:34:19,672 --> 00:34:22,595
they wouldn't make a weapon capable of beating someone to death.

642
00:34:22,678 --> 00:34:25,266
Yeah...
They're just paper, after all.

643
00:34:25,643 --> 00:34:27,395
Then, what about that man?

644
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:28,649
At the hand-washing place,

645
00:34:28,732 --> 00:34:32,155
he said he didn't need the ladle Genta-kun tried to hand him...

646
00:34:32,448 --> 00:34:35,078
Ah, that's definitely it!

647
00:34:35,161 --> 00:34:38,752
There were lots of ladles at that purification basin,

648
00:34:38,835 --> 00:34:42,468
but if an iron ladle had been mixed in among them,

649
00:34:42,843 --> 00:34:45,474
the police would have found it long ago.

650
00:34:45,724 --> 00:34:47,895
Ah... right.

651
00:34:48,145 --> 00:34:50,651
Of course, there was no such ladle.

652
00:34:51,110 --> 00:34:53,740
That leaves only the lady we met at the bell-ringing spot, but...

653
00:34:56,090 --> 00:34:59,385
But there were only two bells.

654
00:35:00,094 --> 00:35:03,180
Hey, before you rang the bell, didn't you do something?

655
00:35:03,305 --> 00:35:04,010
Ah!

656
00:35:04,177 --> 00:35:05,388
Right!

657
00:35:05,472 --> 00:35:06,516
The offering!

658
00:35:06,599 --> 00:35:08,478
We put in 5-yen coins!

659
00:35:08,562 --> 00:35:10,148
Into the offering box!

660
00:35:10,398 --> 00:35:14,782
Yes! Offerings are meant to bring "good luck" or "a good connection,"

661
00:35:14,866 --> 00:35:17,872
so most of them are 5-yen coins with holes.

662
00:35:18,205 --> 00:35:21,963
I see! So, if you thread wire or string through those holes

663
00:35:22,047 --> 00:35:25,386
and bundle a lot together, you get a long, thin stick!

664
00:35:25,804 --> 00:35:28,434
And what's more, even if later on,

665
00:35:28,518 --> 00:35:31,900
a large number of those 5-yen coins were found inside the offering box...

666
00:35:31,983 --> 00:35:34,739
they'd blend in with the other offerings and not arouse suspicion,

667
00:35:34,822 --> 00:35:39,707
tricking the eyes of the police who are searching for a long, thin metal rod!

668
00:35:39,791 --> 00:35:43,255
B-But... to make that into a stick about 30 centimeters long,

669
00:35:43,339 --> 00:35:46,095
you'd need about two hundred 5-yen coins!

670
00:35:46,178 --> 00:35:49,519
And if you threw in that huge amount of 5-yen coins,

671
00:35:49,602 --> 00:35:51,981
it would stand out; people around you would get suspicious!

672
00:35:52,315 --> 00:35:56,198
That's why the culprit spoke to the children.

673
00:35:56,281 --> 00:36:00,749
"If you don't ring the bell loudly, it won't reach the gods," they said.

674
00:36:00,999 --> 00:36:02,670
Huh? Th-Then...

675
00:36:02,753 --> 00:36:04,256
The culprit is...

676
00:36:04,632 --> 00:36:05,843
That's right.

677
00:36:05,926 --> 00:36:07,888
Using the GPS transmitter planted in the wallet

678
00:36:07,972 --> 00:36:11,186
she let the pickpocket steal to track her location...

679
00:36:11,270 --> 00:36:14,902
With a weapon made by bundling a large quantity of 5-yen coins into a stick,

680
00:36:14,986 --> 00:36:16,865
the culprit who beat to death

681
00:36:16,948 --> 00:36:20,622
Ikuyo Yatani, also known as the pickpocket "Kurobe,"

682
00:36:21,541 --> 00:36:23,085
is you!

683
00:36:43,019 --> 00:36:44,689
Huh? Th-Then...

684
00:36:44,772 --> 00:36:45,984
The culprit is...

685
00:36:46,359 --> 00:36:47,611
That's right.

686
00:36:47,695 --> 00:36:49,615
Using the GPS transmitter planted in the wallet

687
00:36:49,699 --> 00:36:52,914
she let the pickpocket steal to track her location...

688
00:36:52,998 --> 00:36:56,671
With a weapon made by bundling a large quantity of 5-yen coins into a stick,

689
00:36:56,754 --> 00:36:58,592
the culprit who beat to death

690
00:36:58,675 --> 00:37:01,932
Ikuyo Yatani, also known as the pickpocket "Kurobe,"

691
00:37:02,641 --> 00:37:05,982
is you! Yoriko Danno-san!

692
00:37:06,357 --> 00:37:08,778
You spoke to the children,

693
00:37:08,863 --> 00:37:11,451
making them ring the bells grandly,

694
00:37:11,534 --> 00:37:15,626
and drowned out the sound of a large amount of 5-yen coins

695
00:37:15,709 --> 00:37:17,004
clinking into the offering box.

696
00:37:17,630 --> 00:37:20,929
If you untie the knot at the base of the string bundling the coins together,

697
00:37:21,012 --> 00:37:24,937
pinch the end of the string, and dangle it into the offering box,

698
00:37:25,062 --> 00:37:28,986
you can deposit a large amount of 5-yen coins in an instant, you see.

699
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:32,034
And what's more, the murder occurred

700
00:37:32,117 --> 00:37:34,330
before you rang the bell.

701
00:37:34,413 --> 00:37:38,588
At that time, your wallet should have already been stolen by the victim,

702
00:37:39,131 --> 00:37:43,807
but the fact that you pretended not to notice and made an offering and rang the bell—

703
00:37:43,891 --> 00:37:45,143
that is the proof.

704
00:37:45,394 --> 00:37:46,813
That's true.

705
00:37:46,897 --> 00:37:48,692
When taking an offering out of your wallet,

706
00:37:48,775 --> 00:37:51,614
you would naturally notice if it had been stolen.

707
00:37:51,698 --> 00:37:53,743
Oh? You don't know?

708
00:37:53,828 --> 00:37:58,211
There's a lesson that says you shouldn't open your wallet in front of the offering box.

709
00:37:58,461 --> 00:38:00,883
If the gods see inside your wallet,

710
00:38:01,134 --> 00:38:04,432
they'll get angry, thinking, "You have that much, yet you're only giving this little?"

711
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:06,019
...so I'm told.

712
00:38:06,561 --> 00:38:09,233
So, when I come to pray,

713
00:38:09,316 --> 00:38:11,738
I keep a 5-yen coin loose in my pocket.

714
00:38:12,072 --> 00:38:13,241
I see.

715
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:17,499
And that's why you didn't notice your wallet was missing?

716
00:38:17,583 --> 00:38:18,668
That's right.

717
00:38:19,086 --> 00:38:22,801
Well, if you're saying you saw me putting a large amount of 5-yen coins

718
00:38:22,886 --> 00:38:26,809
into the offering box, I might admit to it...

719
00:38:26,894 --> 00:38:28,688
We don't need to see it to know.

720
00:38:28,772 --> 00:38:29,774
Huh?

721
00:38:30,358 --> 00:38:33,448
If we examine those shoelaces of yours, that is.

722
00:38:33,824 --> 00:38:35,035
Ah...!

723
00:38:39,543 --> 00:38:43,593
Most likely, what bundled the 5-yen coins together was those shoelaces.

724
00:38:44,637 --> 00:38:48,645
That's why you couldn't leave the crime scene immediately.

725
00:38:48,896 --> 00:38:51,234
Because with one shoelace missing,

726
00:38:51,317 --> 00:38:54,615
your shoe would slip off if you tried to walk normally.

727
00:38:55,033 --> 00:38:57,788
It appears you re-threaded and re-tied your shoelaces after ringing the bell,

728
00:38:57,872 --> 00:39:00,085
but if those shoelaces were used in the crime,

729
00:39:00,168 --> 00:39:03,133
then there should be something on them.

730
00:39:03,843 --> 00:39:05,637
There should be.

731
00:39:06,264 --> 00:39:10,647
Traces of the victim's blood that spattered when she was beaten to death!

732
00:39:16,033 --> 00:39:17,619
Excuse me.

733
00:39:21,127 --> 00:39:23,966
Found it. Bloodstains.

734
00:39:24,633 --> 00:39:26,095
Hmm.

735
00:39:26,179 --> 00:39:29,853
But, why did you have extra black 5-yen coins?

736
00:39:30,437 --> 00:39:33,234
The 5-yen coins left near the body

737
00:39:33,318 --> 00:39:37,576
were the ones slipped into your pocket when you were pickpocketed this time...

738
00:39:37,659 --> 00:39:41,375
Those are the ones I showed you, the police, earlier.

739
00:39:41,626 --> 00:39:45,342
Huh? Then, those 5-yen coins...

740
00:39:46,135 --> 00:39:50,477
The ones I placed beside her were the ones slipped into my pocket

741
00:39:51,020 --> 00:39:53,650
when that pickpocket stole from me last year—

742
00:39:54,735 --> 00:39:57,115
the 5-yen coins that stole my son's life!

743
00:39:57,449 --> 00:39:58,451
Huh?!

744
00:39:58,785 --> 00:40:00,205
Your son...?

745
00:40:00,288 --> 00:40:03,879
Could it be... the one in the photo booth sticker inside your wallet...?

746
00:40:05,967 --> 00:40:08,137
Yes, that's right.

747
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:11,602
Last year, the wallet that pickpocket stole from me

748
00:40:11,686 --> 00:40:13,648
also had my car key inside.

749
00:40:14,066 --> 00:40:15,443
Because it was missing,

750
00:40:15,527 --> 00:40:19,828
my son, who had asthma, was trapped inside the car for several hours.

751
00:40:20,078 --> 00:40:21,664
Getting him to the hospital was delayed,

752
00:40:22,416 --> 00:40:25,171
and in the end, he died.

753
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:30,307
So, I researched that pickpocket online like crazy,

754
00:40:30,724 --> 00:40:33,354
and staked out places she was likely to appear.

755
00:40:34,315 --> 00:40:36,903
But, why a photo booth sticker?

756
00:40:36,987 --> 00:40:39,033
Well... thanks to that sticker,

757
00:40:39,116 --> 00:40:42,039
we were able to identify it as your wallet, but...

758
00:40:42,748 --> 00:40:44,878
If she opened the wallet to take out the money,

759
00:40:45,545 --> 00:40:48,134
that sticker would catch her eye whether she liked it or not, right?

760
00:40:49,053 --> 00:40:52,642
I wanted to force that pickpocket to see it.

761
00:40:53,728 --> 00:40:56,150
That what you stole wasn't just money.

762
00:40:57,361 --> 00:41:01,243
It was also the life of one little boy...

763
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:10,011
So... can I go home now?

764
00:41:10,095 --> 00:41:12,432
Yes.
Then, I'll be going too.

765
00:41:12,892 --> 00:41:15,021
Since there's also the pickpocketing matter,

766
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:18,277
we may need to ask you some more questions at a later date.

767
00:41:18,361 --> 00:41:20,323
Ah, that's fine.

768
00:41:20,407 --> 00:41:21,910
Please get in touch.

769
00:41:21,993 --> 00:41:23,956
Hey, mister...
Hm?

770
00:41:24,289 --> 00:41:27,087
Mister, by any chance, do you have bad eyesight?

771
00:41:27,170 --> 00:41:28,589
Huh? Why do you ask?

772
00:41:28,924 --> 00:41:30,802
Because... that pickpocket lady

773
00:41:30,886 --> 00:41:33,433
looked surprised when she saw your face.

774
00:41:33,516 --> 00:41:36,272
I think that's because the person she'd just pickpocketed a little while ago

775
00:41:36,355 --> 00:41:38,776
was you, mister, but...

776
00:41:39,319 --> 00:41:42,325
Why didn't you say anything back then?

777
00:41:42,409 --> 00:41:44,873
Even though it should have been the second time you met that lady.

778
00:41:44,956 --> 00:41:48,713
Y-You see... I have bad eyesight,

779
00:41:48,796 --> 00:41:52,637
If your eyesight's bad, shouldn't you be wearing glasses? You can't see the cherry blossoms!

780
00:41:53,181 --> 00:41:55,435
Did you come flower viewing by yourself?

781
00:41:55,518 --> 00:41:58,024
Actually, I came to buy a protective charm.

782
00:41:58,107 --> 00:42:00,695
What kind of charm?
Huh...

783
00:42:01,155 --> 00:42:03,284
A charm for me, right?

784
00:42:03,367 --> 00:42:04,703
M-Motoe...

785
00:42:05,246 --> 00:42:06,707
Heh heh.

786
00:42:08,794 --> 00:42:10,089
It's for this little one.

787
00:42:10,173 --> 00:42:12,010
Ah, a baby!

788
00:42:12,093 --> 00:42:14,431
It's a charm for a safe delivery, right?

789
00:42:14,515 --> 00:42:16,769
I told you to stay put at home.

790
00:42:17,354 --> 00:42:21,487
You weren't coming back at all, so I got worried and came to check on you, didn't I?

791
00:42:21,570 --> 00:42:26,205
So, could you be... the one who put duct tape on me

792
00:42:26,288 --> 00:42:28,084
during that bank robbery...?

793
00:42:28,584 --> 00:42:31,925
Oh? The foreigner from back then?

794
00:42:32,008 --> 00:42:35,933
I'm so sorry about that. I was threatened and had no choice...

795
00:42:36,225 --> 00:42:37,769
Ugh...
Ah!

796
00:42:39,983 --> 00:42:41,819
Oh! Are you alright?!

797
00:42:45,285 --> 00:42:46,997
Heh... heh heh...

798
00:42:50,545 --> 00:42:51,965
S-Sorry.

799
00:42:52,048 --> 00:42:55,973
With my wife's condition and all, is it alright if we leave now?

800
00:42:56,056 --> 00:42:57,350
Ah... yes...

801
00:43:00,273 --> 00:43:03,779
Morning sickness is a symptom seen in early pregnancy, right?

802
00:43:03,864 --> 00:43:06,535
Yeah... but, with a belly that size,

803
00:43:06,619 --> 00:43:09,124
I'd think she's about six months along.

804
00:43:09,499 --> 00:43:13,049
Well, the nausea could be from other causes, too.

805
00:43:13,925 --> 00:43:15,971
Yes... that's right, Camel.

806
00:43:16,055 --> 00:43:19,353
It seems that burned man wasn't Shu, after all.

807
00:43:19,436 --> 00:43:22,317
I guess it was a decoy they set up

808
00:43:22,609 --> 00:43:25,740
to see whether Shu was really dead.

809
00:43:25,824 --> 00:43:28,120
Ah, Jodie-san!
Ah!

810
00:43:28,204 --> 00:43:31,710
Anyway, I'll give you the details when I get back there.

811
00:43:32,545 --> 00:43:37,138
The money's probably been taken, but please check the contents of your wallet.

812
00:43:37,222 --> 00:43:38,307
Right.

813
00:43:40,603 --> 00:43:44,403
All the cards are here, and inside my pocket, too...

814
00:43:44,695 --> 00:43:45,697
Ah!

815
00:43:46,448 --> 00:43:49,371
This is... from that time during the department store hijacking...

816
00:43:52,544 --> 00:43:53,546
Hm?

817
00:43:54,548 --> 00:43:57,303
Huh? The coaster's corner is folded over.

818
00:43:58,974 --> 00:44:00,143
Ha...!

819
00:44:00,894 --> 00:44:03,566
"Run. This area is dangerous."

820
00:44:05,988 --> 00:44:07,198
Shu...

821
00:44:09,035 --> 00:44:10,329
Shu...

822
00:44:11,457 --> 00:44:12,667
Shu...

823
00:44:14,755 --> 00:44:17,677
If that burned man isn't Shu,

824
00:44:18,847 --> 00:44:22,479
then who on earth... and for what purpose...?

825
00:44:24,608 --> 00:44:27,447
Sorry, Jodie Agent.

826
00:44:28,783 --> 00:44:34,795
♪~

827
00:45:42,639 --> 00:45:48,400
~♪

828
00:45:53,202 --> 00:45:54,914
Huff...

829
00:45:54,997 --> 00:45:58,504
Hm? Hey, mister, if you sleep in a place like this,

830
00:45:58,587 --> 00:46:00,675
you'll catch a... Huh?!

831
00:46:02,637 --> 00:46:04,557
H-Hey, you...

832
00:46:04,641 --> 00:46:08,107
It's fine. He's just drunk and sleeping it off.

833
00:46:08,190 --> 00:46:11,071
Huh?!
My brother's a lightweight.

834
00:46:11,154 --> 00:46:14,536
Huh? T... Twins?!

835
00:46:20,131 --> 00:46:22,552
That was an unexpected turn of events, wasn't it?

836
00:46:22,635 --> 00:46:26,518
To think the man we used for the disguise had been pickpocketed...

837
00:46:26,601 --> 00:46:30,861
I did think it was odd he wasn't carrying a wallet, though.

838
00:46:31,403 --> 00:46:35,327
Well, it was a good thing I borrowed those strange 5-yen coins

839
00:46:35,411 --> 00:46:37,958
that were slipped into his pocket.

840
00:46:38,042 --> 00:46:42,759
But going out of your way to return that stolen wallet to him...

841
00:46:43,260 --> 00:46:46,266
If it caused a big commotion later, that would be a problem, right?

842
00:46:46,349 --> 00:46:48,771
It had his cash card and driver's license, after all.

843
00:46:49,355 --> 00:46:52,153
Well, be grateful.

844
00:46:52,236 --> 00:46:54,282
When that FBI kitten

845
00:46:54,699 --> 00:46:59,250
grabbed you by the arm, the listening device you planted on her cuff...

846
00:47:00,211 --> 00:47:02,423
I made sure to retrieve it for you.

847
00:47:02,799 --> 00:47:04,511
Thanks for that.

848
00:47:04,761 --> 00:47:06,014
So?

849
00:47:08,060 --> 00:47:10,189
From that kitten...

850
00:47:10,272 --> 00:47:13,863
Heh heh heh... Were you able to hear anything good?

851
00:47:14,239 --> 00:47:17,411
Yes... it was a major haul.

852
00:47:18,539 --> 00:47:20,877
And I overheard an unexpected inside story, as well.

853
00:47:21,128 --> 00:47:25,846
You will let me hear the punchline of that story properly, won't you?

854
00:47:25,929 --> 00:47:28,642
Yes. As soon as I have confirmation.

855
00:47:29,394 --> 00:47:31,815
But, let me just say this one thing.

856
00:47:31,899 --> 00:47:33,026
Hm?

857
00:47:34,028 --> 00:47:36,283
He's a terrifying man.

858
00:47:39,747 --> 00:47:41,710
That boy.

859
00:47:44,174 --> 00:47:47,890
So, you still just can't accept Mouri-kun's reasoning, can you?

860
00:47:47,973 --> 00:47:50,352
Ah, so that's it, after all.

861
00:47:50,436 --> 00:47:52,607
That left hand means...

862
00:47:53,483 --> 00:47:56,239
Crap! I need to let her know, fast!

863
00:47:58,410 --> 00:47:59,621
No good!

864
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:07,678
Kaori-san...! Ah...!

865
00:48:07,678 --> 00:48:13,178
Next Conan:
"A Coded Invitation"

866
00:48:14,078 --> 00:48:16,178
Next Conan Hint:

867
00:48:16,178 --> 00:48:18,278
"Left Hand"

868
00:48:18,400 --> 00:48:20,310
Solve the riddle of the mysterious party!

869
00:48:20,477 --> 00:48:21,854
Detective Conan: The Coded Invitation!

870
00:48:21,894 --> 00:48:30,000
Airs at 6 PM on Saturday 19th April!
